# Exercise 02: Apply security and governance controls for the AI app

### Estimated Duration: 45 Minutes

## Scenario

Your Azure AI application is now deployed, but it still needs security controls that protect the app, its supporting data, and the AI interaction surface. In this exercise, you will use Microsoft Defender for Cloud as the primary security plane to review recommendations and enable key protections for App Service, Storage, and AI services. You will then use Microsoft Purview as a supporting governance control to confirm that AI interaction data can be governed and investigated as part of a broader secure AI lifecycle.

## Overview

In this exercise, you will sign in to Azure, review the deployed AI application resources, enable and inspect Defender-related protections, and validate the governance connection for AI interactions through Purview. The tasks are designed to align to the deployed Azure App Service, Azure OpenAI, and Azure Storage resources associated with **<inject key="DeploymentID" enableCopy="false"></inject>**.

## Objectives

- Task 1: Sign in and locate the deployed AI application resources
- Task 2: Enable and verify Defender protections for Storage and AI services
- Task 3: Review and improve App Service security posture in Defender for Cloud
- Task 4: Validate the supporting Purview governance outcome for AI interactions

