## Task 2: Enable and verify Defender protections for Storage and AI services

In this task, you will use Microsoft Defender for Cloud to enable or confirm protection for the storage and AI portions of the application.

1. In the Azure portal search bar, search for **Microsoft Defender for Cloud** and open it.
2. From the left menu, select **Environment settings**.
3. Select the subscription **<inject key="SubscriptionID"></inject>**.
4. Review the **Defender plans** page.
5. Locate the **Storage** plan.
6. If the Storage plan is not already enabled, select the ellipsis (**...**) or choose **Settings** as available in the current experience, then turn **Storage** to **On** and save the change.
7. After enabling the plan, review the available Storage protection settings and note that **on-upload malware scanning** and **sensitive data threat detection** are part of Defender for Storage.
8. Still in the Defender plans area, locate **AI services**.
9. Turn **AI services** to **On** if it is not already enabled.
10. Select **Settings** for **AI services**.
11. Review the available AI protection components.
12. Confirm that the AI services protection configuration includes options such as:
    - **Suspicious prompt evidence**
    - **Enable data security for AI interactions**
    - **AI model security**
13. Enable **Enable data security for AI interactions** if it is available and currently turned off.
14. Select **Continue** or **Save** to apply the AI services settings.
15. Return to the storage account tab that you opened earlier.
16. In the storage account left menu, under **Security + networking**, select **Microsoft Defender for Cloud**.
17. Confirm that Defender for Storage is enabled for the storage account and review any account-level settings that are shown.
18. Record that the storage account is now under Defender-backed protection for malware scanning and sensitive data threat detection.

> [!Important]
> Microsoft Learn recommends enabling Defender for Storage at the subscription level so that current and future storage accounts in the subscription are protected consistently.

> [!Note]
> The Purview-related AI interaction setting is a supporting governance capability. In many organizations, its visibility depends on the correct licensing and tenant configuration, but the required control in this lab is to verify and enable the Defender-side integration point when available.

## Task 3: Review and improve App Service security posture in Defender for Cloud

In this task, you will review Defender for Cloud recommendations that apply to the App Service workload and then confirm key hardening settings directly on the web app.

1. Return to **Microsoft Defender for Cloud**.
2. In the left menu, select **Recommendations**.
3. Use the filters to narrow the list to the lab resource group or to **Resource type** entries related to **App Service**, **Web Apps**, or the deployed web app resource.
4. Review the recommendations that apply to the App Service resource.
5. Look for recommendations commonly associated with App Service hardening, such as:
   - **Web Application should only be accessible over HTTPS**
   - **TLS should be updated to the latest version for web apps**
   - **Managed identity should be used in your Web App**
   - **Remote debugging should be turned off for Web Applications**
   - **Microsoft Defender for App Service should be enabled**
6. Open the deployed App Service resource.
7. In the App Service left menu, under **Settings**, select **Configuration**.
8. On the **General settings** tab, verify the following settings:
   - **HTTPS Only** is set to **On**
   - **Minimum TLS Version** is set to **1.2** or later if that option is available in the lab environment
   - **Remote debugging** is **Off** if the setting is present
9. If any of these settings are not configured to the secure value, update them now and select **Save**.
10. In the App Service left menu, select **Identity**.
11. On the **System assigned** tab, turn **Status** to **On** if it is currently **Off**.
12. Select **Save**.
13. Wait for the identity assignment to complete.
14. Return to **Microsoft Defender for Cloud** and refresh the recommendations view if needed.
15. Confirm that your web app now reflects a stronger security posture, even if recommendation status changes take additional time to update.

> [!Tip]
> Defender recommendations can take time to refresh after a remediation. If a recommendation still appears immediately after you apply a change, wait a few minutes and refresh the page.

